text: Roy Jansen Roy Jansen (born 6 May 1950) is a Norwegian ice hockey player. He was born in Oslo, Norway and represented the clubs IL Sparta and Vålerengens IF. He played for the Norwegian national ice hockey team, and participated at the Winter Olympics in Sapporo in 1972, where the Norwegian team placed 8th. == References == Category:1950 births Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Oslo Category:Ice hockey players at the 1972 Winter Olympics Category:Norwegian ice hockey players Category:Olympic ice hockey players of Norway Category:Vålerenga Ishockey players
